We can also conclude that The x-axis is neatly arranged in terms of date because an xts is a timeseries object in r which extensively works with time based data, taking in consideration its periodicity, etc.

Ans4: After applying auto arima with no seasonality, we can see the order of the model is (0,1,2). Therefore, p=0,d=1,q=2.

Ans5: Auto arima in the previous question returned d=1, which mean we had to take first differencing to make the series stationary. In case of a stationary series, d will be 0. Our EDA analysis concluded that the time series is non-stationary, which is confirmed by d.

Mean percentage error is non-zero but is close to zero which shows a good forecast. Mean absolute percentage error is low as well which indicates a reliable forecast.

Ans8: Model-1 emulates a random walk with drift, with p=0, d=1, q=1. So this series is non-stationary and it changes randomly from one observation to the next, however, since p=0, it is not autoregressive. Model-2 has a random walk with drift behaviour and short term autocorrelation (p=1).

##                ME     RMSE      MAE      MPE     MAPE

##                ME     RMSE     MAE      MPE     MAPE

Ans9: The above shows forecast and accuracy for both the models. The accuracy of the forecast is compared with the actual test series.

Ans10.1: Root mean squared error for Model-2 is better than that of Model-1. p is 0 in Model-1 and 1 in Model-2. Since higher value of p helps capture the longer term dependency in the series, we can note that the series has longer term dependencies that we need to capture. Also, we can note that Model-2 has an unchanged q=2 as the original model, which could’ve helped capture short term dependencies (moving average).

## [1] -0.02181436

## [1] -0.02716629

Ans10.2:Both values of ACF1 are negative which means that the forecast errors have a negative correlation at lag 1. This means that if the forecast overestimates the value of the time series at a particular time point, then it is more likely to underestimate the value at the next time point, and vice versa. For reference, the ACF1 of the original model with p=0, d=1, and q=2 was positive but close to 0 (~0.010). Hence the original model gave us the most accurate forcast, compared to Model-1 and Model-2.
